To call QBF with no parameters:
```
commit;
call qbf();
```
This will display the QBF catalog frame.

Here's an example of calling QBF with specific parameters:
```
commit;
call qbf(qbfname = 'expenses', flags = '-mappend -s');
```
This runs QBF in insert mode, suppressing status messages, using the QBFName 'expenses'.

To call a report:
```
commit;
call report(name = 'emptable', mode = 'column');
```
This runs a default report on 'emptable' in column mode.

Here's an example of calling a report with complex parameters:
```
create table :tbl as select * from orders where status = :status and custno = :custno;
commit;
call report(name = 'orders', param = 'table = "' + :tbl + '"');
```
This creates a temporary table and runs a report on it, passing the table name as a parameter.

To call an OpenROAD application from an image file:
```
commit;
call runimage(filename = 'runimage', startcomponent = 'framename');
```
This calls the application in 'runimage', starting at the frame specified in 'framename'.

Here's an example of error handling with a call statement:
```
call rundbapp(application = 'inventory', startcomponent = 'parts');
if CurSession.CallSystemStatus != 0 then
    message 'Error calling inventory application: ' || char(CurSession.CallSystemStatus);
endif;
```
This checks the CurSession.CallSystemStatus after the call to handle any errors.
